\section{Conclusion}

The Hamiltonian Crystal framework unifies integer Fock states, topologically protected spectral gaps, Riemann-inspired structures, time-crystal oscillations, and dark-sector couplings. It provides a concrete and falsifiable approach to vacuum energy, black hole microstates, and possible experimental signatures via oscillatory phenomena and portal interactions.

